      • delete

        void delete(String nsGroupId,
          Boolean force)
        Deletes the specified NSGroup. By default, if the NSGroup is added to another NSGroup, it won't be deleted. In such situations, pass \"force=true\" as query param to force delete the NSGroup.

        Synchronous method overload. Result of the invocation will be reported as a method return value.

        Parameters:
        nsGroupId - NSGroup Id (required)
        force - Force delete the resource even if it is being used somewhere (optional, default to false)

      • list

        NSGroupListResult list(String cursor,
                     String includedFields,
                     String memberTypes,
                     Long pageSize,
                     Boolean populateReferences,
                     Boolean sortAscending,
                     String sortBy)
        List the NSGroups in a paginated format. The page size is restricted to 50 NSGroups so that the size of the response remains small even in the worst case. Optionally, specify valid member types as request parameter to filter NSGroups.

        Synchronous method overload. Result of the invocation will be reported as a method return value.

        Parameters:
        cursor - Opaque cursor to be used for getting next page of records (supplied by current result page) (optional)
        includedFields - Comma separated list of fields that should be included in query result (optional)
        memberTypes - Specify member types to filter corresponding NSGroups (optional)
        pageSize - Maximum number of results to return in this page (server may return fewer) (optional, default to 1000)
        populateReferences - Populate metadata of resource referenced by NSGroupExpressions (optional, default to false)
        sortAscending - (optional)
        sortBy - Field by which records are sorted (optional)
        Returns:
        com.vmware.nsx.model.NSGroupListResult
        Throws:
        ServiceUnavailable - Service Unavailable
        InvalidRequest - Bad Request, Precondition Failed
